  "prompt": "Can you be a pilot if you wear glasses?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be a pilot if you wear glasses. Many pilots wear corrective lenses, including glasses and contact lenses, to meet the vision requirements set by aviation authorities. \n\nFor example, the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) in the United States requires that a pilot\u2019s vision be at least 20/20 in one eye and 20/40 in the other eye, with or without corrective lenses. As long as you meet these vision standards with your glasses or contacts, you can obtain the necessary medical certification to fly.\n\nIt's important to have your vision evaluated as part of the medical examination required for pilot certification. If you have any specific conditions related to your eyesight, it's advisable to discuss these with an aviation medical examiner.",
